{"id":1889,"date":"2018-08-19T21:57:13","date_gmt":"2018-08-20T04:57:13","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/?page_id=1889"},"modified":"2020-05-24T17:00:50","modified_gmt":"2020-05-24T17:00:50","slug":"skywalker","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/skywalker\/","title":{"rendered":"skywalker: things I like in python"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><code>skywalker<\/code> is a Python module which contains some of the things I like in python. I was tired of copying the same snippets over and over, so I put them in a module to be imported from everywhere. <code>skywalker<\/code> is compatible with both python 2 and 3, and deals with all sort of things like plotting, timing, checkpointing, etc. etc.<\/p>\n\n<h2>Installation<\/h2>\n\n<pre><code>pip install skywalker\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<h2>Useful links<\/h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Repository: <a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/dgerosa\/skywalker\">github.com\/dgerosa\/skywalker<\/a><\/li>\n<li>Documentation: <a href=\"http:\/\/dgerosa.github.io\/skywalker\">dgerosa.github.io\/skywalker<\/a><\/li>\n<li>Webpage: <a href=\"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/skywalker\/\">davidegerosa.com\/skywalker\/<\/a><\/li>\n<li>Python Package Index: <a href=\"https:\/\/pypi.org\/project\/skywalker\/\">pypi.org\/project\/skywalker<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h2>Tools<\/h2>\n\n<p>These are some of the things you can do with <code>skywalker<\/code> (beside using a lightsaber, of course).  A list of all functions and tools is available in the documentation.<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>checkpoint<\/strong>: Smart checkpointing of function outputs to <code>h5<\/code> files.<\/li>\n<li><strong>dontprint<\/strong>: Deep output suppression.<\/li>\n<li><strong>plot<\/strong>: Handle matplotlib options, including saving to file.<\/li>\n<li><strong>processify<\/strong>: Spawn a new process everytime that function is executed.<\/li>\n<li><strong>singleton<\/strong>: Define that class as a singleton (one instance at any time can exist)<\/li>\n<li><strong>timer<\/strong>: Print execution time of a function\/class.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h2>Cite me<\/h2>\n\n<p>If you want to cite this code: <a href=\"https:\/\/zenodo.org\/badge\/latestdoi\/134632789\"><img src=\"https:\/\/zenodo.org\/badge\/134632789.svg\" alt=\"DOI\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":2551,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_coblocks_attr":"","_coblocks_dimensions":"","_coblocks_responsive_height":"","_coblocks_accordion_ie_support":"","_mi_skip_tracking":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_active":false,"_monsterinsights_sitenote_note":"","_monsterinsights_sitenote_category":0,"footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1889"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1889"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1889\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":3414,"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/1889\/revisions\/3414"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/2551"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1889"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}